 Alex Salmond has stepped up the pressure on Ed Miliband saying he wo n't be able to avoid a deal with the SNP and was ` foolish ' to rule out a coalition .
The former SNP leader said the Labour leader would find it difficult to avoid doing a deal to the Scottish nationalists in the event of hung parliament .
SNP leader Nicola Sturgeon says Mr Miliband would not be forgiven if he allowed David Cameron back into Downing Street .